    "caption": "A tiny leaf-eating machine with a wild transformation ahead.",
    "shortDescription": "Caterpillars have one job: eat. They chew through leaves almost constantly, growing so fast they might shed their skin several times before becoming a butterfly or moth. Inside the chrysalis, their entire body literally dissolves into a kind of living soup before rebuilding itself completely. Fun fact: Some caterpillars have fake eyespots on their bodies to look like much bigger, scarier animals to frighten away birds."
